      "process.command_line",
      "process.parent.name"
    ],
    "notes": "Detection should focus on: (1) sc.exe invocations with 'binPath=' pointing outside of System32/Program Files/ProgramData vendor subdirs, (2) services.exe spawning child processes from C:\\ProgramData\\ or user-writable paths, (3) service binary paths that do not match signed/expected vendor locations. Key differentiator between attack and benign: executable path — attack binary lives in C:\\ProgramData\\WindowsUpdate\\ (writable, non-standard), while benign services live under C:\\Windows\\ or C:\\Program Files\\. Fawkes uses service execution as a persistence and execution primitive via its 'service' command."
  },
